Residents in Mahikeng in the North West say they’re simply tired of poor service delivery. They’re calling on Premier Job Mokgoro’s administration to address their concerns. eNCA's Khayelihle Khumalo has more. Courtesy #DStv403 MAHIKENG - Residents in Mahikeng in the North West say they’re simply tired of poor service delivery. They’re calling on Premier Job Mokgoro’s administration to address their concerns. READ: Mokgoro says serving NW residents remains his priority Mokgoro delivered his state of the province address where he says the local government is working to fix broken municipalities. But residents say time is running out.